classitems.description: Add a new pattern for recognizing dates
classitems.name: addPattern

params.name: spec
params.description: An array containing 3 items: [name, regex, function or replace pattern]

params.name: afterName
params.description: The named pattern after which to add this pattern. When not given, place pattern at beginning

example:
Date.addPattern(['month-year', /^(\d{1,2})-(\d{4})$/, '$1/01/$2']);
	Date.addPattern(['hoy', /^hoy$/i, function(match) { return new Date(); }], 'iso_8601');

classitems.description: Remove a pattern by name
classitems.name: removePattern

params.name: name
params.description: The name of the pattern to remove

return.description: Returns the removed pattern or false if pattern not found

example:
Date.removePattern('us'); // us-style m/d/Y dates no longer recognized
	var us = Date.removePattern('us'); Date.addPattern(us, 'world'); // prefer world-style d/m/Y dates over us-style dates
